{{short description|Chinese Buddhist encyclopedic work}}
{{italic title}}
{{unreferenced|date=July 2012}}
'''''Fayuan Zhulin''''' ({{zh|c=法苑珠林|p=Fǎyuàn Zhūlín}}; "Forest of Gems in the Garden of the [[Dharma]]"), in 100 ''juan'' (卷 "volume", "fascicle"), is a [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] [[encyclopedia]] compiled AD 668 by [[Dao Shi]] (道世). It comprises Buddhist and other ancient texts otherwise lost, and is thus an important source of ancient knowledge in many fields.
It was used under the [[Ming Dynasty]] to reconstruct older [[zhiguai]] collections.

